North%20America.%20The%20finding%20came%20courtesy%20of%20ancient%20DNA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELindsey%20said%20the%20news%20was%20surprising%20because%20they're%20so%20similar%20behaviorally%20and%20morphologically.%20For%20example%2C%20they%20likely%20lived%20in%20packs%20like%20modern%20dogs%2C%20wolves%2C%20and%20coyotes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20know%20quite%20a%20bit%20about%20how%20dire%20wolves%20hunted%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BScientists%20have%20looked%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdire-wolf-and-sabre-tooth-cat-bones-show-what-prehistoric-hunts-were-like-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einjuries%20in%20dire%20wolves%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20saber-tooth%20cats%2C%20that%20were%20found%20in%20the%20tar%20pits%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindsey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20found%20injuries%20to%20the%20fossils'%20paws%20and%20skulls.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20consistent%20with%20the%20type%20of%20injuries%20we%20see%20in%2C%20say%2C%20wolves%20today%20that%20are%20chasing%20down%20animals%20on%20the%20landscape%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindsey%20said.%20A%20wolf's%20prey%20might%20trample%20its%20toes%20or%20kick%20it%20in%20the%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESaber-tooth%20cats%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222185%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20child%20crouches%20under%20a%20replica%20of%20a%20saber-tooth%20cat%20at%20the%20National%20Museum%20of%20Scotland%20in%20Edinburgh%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d9d8cb788914e5553b7c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20types%20of%20saber-tooth%20cats%20had%20teeth%20as%20long%20as%207%20inches.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Milligan%2FPA%20Images%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHeight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%203%20feet%20at%20the%20shoulder%20(smilodon%20and%20scimitar)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20300%20to%20500%20pounds%20(scimitar%20cat)%3B%20up%20to%20750%20pounds%20(smilodon)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20did%20they%20go%20extinct%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERoughly%2010%2C000%20years%20ago%20(smilodon)%3B%20between%2010%2C000%20and%2028%2C000%20years%20ago%20(scimitar)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20have%20grown%20up%20calling%20them%20saber-toothed%20tigers%2C%20but%20the%20smilodon%20isn't%20a%20close%20relative%20of%20tigers.%20Their%20common%20name%20comes%20from%20their%20impressive%20canine%20teeth%2C%20which%20could%20be%20up%20to%207%20inches%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20genus%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdire-wolf-and-sabre-tooth-cat-bones-show-what-prehistoric-hunts-were-like-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaber-tooth%20cats%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Homotherium%2C%20is%20known%20as%20scimitar%20cats.%20Their%20teeth%20weren't%20as%20long%20as%20smilodon%20and%20were%20serrated%20like%20a%20steak%20knife.%20Like%20the%20smilodon%2C%20they%20lived%20in%20North%20America%20during%20the%20Pleistocene.%20The%20two%20cats%20were%20similarly%20widespread%2C%20from%20the%20Yukon%20to%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20two%20predators%20had%20different%20prey%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fcurrent-biology%2Ffulltext%2FS0960-9822(21)00434-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20study%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20While%20the%20smilodon%20went%20after%20tapirs%20(pig-like%20animals%20with%20trunks)%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20deer%2C%20scimitars%20preferred%20baby%20mammoths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSaber-tooth%20cats%20tend%20to%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20injuries%20in%20their%20lower%20back%2C%20which%20is%20consistent%20with%20this%20idea%20that%20they%20were%20ambush%20predators%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindsey%20said.%20The%20smilodons%20would%20sit%20and%20wait%20before%20leaping%20onto%20a%20large%20animal%20and%20wrestling%20it%20to%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20easy%20to%20torque%20your%20back%20that%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindsey%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20they%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20lower%20back%20arthritis%20type%20of%20injuries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELindsey%20was%20also%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D42246614699244699707dd7c242788d80d4a91432fafa7103792e8fe2d509dd0%26postID%3D654c1e6cb0b368bea7429e8a%26postSlug%3Dextinct-giant-mammals-pleistocene-megafauna-ice-age-north-america%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-021-99853-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20study%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20diagnosed%20a%20smilodon%20with%20hip%20dysplasia%20based%20on%20a%20CT%20scan%20of%20a%20fossil.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20animal%20that%20probably%20couldn't%20have%20survived%20to%20adulthood%20as%20it%20did%20without%20other%20animals%20taking%20care%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20that%20indicates%20that%20these%20are%20probably%20social%20creatures.%20There's%20all%20kinds%20of%20amazing%2C%20fun%20things%20you%20can%20learn%20from%20bones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGiant%20sloths%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Visitors%20look%20at%20a%20large%20skeleton%20of%20a%20giant%20ground%20sloth%20in%20a%20museum%20in%20Florida%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d9f363cc84b4dfaffd99e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGiant%20ground%20sloths%20lived%20up%20to%20their%20names.%20They%20were%20huge%20and%20didn't%20live%20in%20trees%20like%20their%20modern%20descendants.%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20Greenberg%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHeight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2019.6%20feet%20when%20upright%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Up%20to%203%20tons%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20did%20they%20go%20extinct%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E10%2C000%20years%20ago%20or%20into%20the%20Late%20Holocene%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20extinct%20Pleistocene%20megafauna%20%E2%80%94%20animals%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froyalsocietypublishing.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1098%2Frspb.2019.2643%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eweighing%20more%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20100%20pounds%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%20still%20living%20analogs.%20Instead%20of%20mammoths%2C%20there%20are%20elephants.%20Camelops%20has%20its%20camel%20and%20llama%20relatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20you%20don't%20have%20anything%20in%20the%20world%20that%20is%20even%20kind%20of%20like%20a%203%2C000-pound%20sloth%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindsey%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20just%20something%20that%20is%20completely%20gone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20their%20modern%20counterparts%2C%20these%20behemoths%20spent%20most%20of%20their%20time%20on%20the%20ground%20instead%20of%20in%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorth%20America%20had%20several%20species%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgiant-sloths-hunted-by-humans-bones-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egiant%20sloths%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Among%20the%20largest%20were%20the%20Eremotherium%2C%20which%20have%20mostly%20been%20found%20in%20the%20southeast%20along%20Florida%20and%20the%20Gulf%20Coast%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20Central%20and%20South%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20like%20sort%20of%20the%20wetter%2C%20more%20tropical%20regions%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindsey%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20got%20to%20be%20about%20the%20size%20of%20elephants.%26quot%3B%20While%20very%20large%2C%20the%20Eremotherium%20wasn't%20as%20big%20as%20the%20Megatherium%20%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eanother%20species%20of%20giant%20sloth%20%E2%80%94%20which%20lived%20throughout%20South%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffossils-of-giant-sloth-found-in-sinkhole-2019-3%