ombining%20Western%20and%20Soviet%20air-defense%20systems%20is%20known%20as%20the%20FrankenSAM%20program.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20its%20air%20defenses%20working%20overtime%20to%20defend%20against%20constant%20Russian%20strikes%2C%20Ukraine%20is%20working%20with%20the%20US%20to%20create%20new%20capabilities%20by%20cobbling%20together%20Western%20and%20Soviet%20systems%20that%20weren't%20built%20to%20play%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20Frankensteinian%20effort%2C%20often%20combining%20American%20missiles%20with%20Soviet%20launchers%20or%20radars%20or%20reviving%20and%20modernizing%20Cold%20War%20technology%2C%20appears%20to%20be%20working%2C%20showing%20signs%20it%20could%20help%20boost%20Ukraine's%20defenses%20at%20a%20critical%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20weekend%2C%20Ukrainian%20Air%20Force%20spokesperson%20Yurii%20Ihnat%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20that%20Ukraine%20had%20successfully%20converted%20a%20Soviet%20air%20defense%20system%20to%20fire%20US-provided%20missiles%20and%20was%20testing%20the%20combination%20on%20American%20soil%2C%20explaining%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20good%20results%20of%20the%20combat%20use%20of%20Buk-M1%20anti-aircraft%20missile%20systems%20on%20the%20training%20ground%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20which%20have%20been%20converted%20and%20adapted%20to%20American%20missiles%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkyivindependent.com%2Fair-force-ukraine-can-adapt-soviet-air-defense-systems-to-fire-u-s-missiles%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20report%20from%20the%20Kyiv%20Independent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesting%20has%20been%20underway%20over%20the%20last%20few%20months%20and%20has%20included%20pairing%20Buks%20with%20US-provided%20RIM-7%20Sea%20Sparrow%20missiles%20and%20Soviet-era%20radars%20with%20American%20AIM-9M%20Sidewinder%20missiles%2C%20US%20officials%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F28%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fair-defense-ukraine-frankensam.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20late%20October.%20Reporting%20earlier%20this%20year%20indicated%20Ukraine%20had%20found%20ways%20to%20modify%20the%20Soviet%20Buk%20air%20defenses%20to%20fire%20the%20RIM-7.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIhnat%20said%20that%20Ukraine%20has%20had%20to%20adapt%20its%20Soviet%20defense%20systems%20to%20carry%20other%20missiles%20due%20to%20limited%20supplies%20and%20an%20obvious%20inability%20to%20get%20new%20ones%20from%20Russia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20its%20Western%20allies%20have%20offered%20Ukraine%20air%20defenses%20like%20Patriot%20batteries%2C%20IRIS-T%2C%20NASAMs%2C%20and%20Gepard%20anti-aircraft%20guns%2C%20but%20Ukrainian%20forces%20continue%20to%20operate%20a%20number%20of%20Soviet%20air%20defenses%2C%20the%20Buk%20and%20the%20S-300%20being%20among%20the%20most%20prominent.%20But%20they're%20running%20low%20on%20missiles%2C%20expending%20them%20at%20rapid%20rates%20to%20counter%20Russian%20airstrikes%20and%20drone%20attacks.%20The%20US%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20has%20plenty%20of%20Sea%20Sparrows%20and%20other%20SAMs%20to%20offer.%20The%20challenge%20is%20how%20to%20adapt%20both%20to%20work%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amphibious%20assault%20ship%20USS%20Bonhomme%20Richard%20(LHD%206)%20fires%20a%20NATO%20Sea%20Sparrow%20surface-to-air%20missile%20to%20intercept%20a%20remote-controlled%20drone%20as%20part%20of%20Valiant%20Shield%202016%20(VS16).%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6553bbe64ca513d82429235a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222086%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmphibious%20assault%20ship%20USS%20Bonhomme%20Richard%20(LHD%206)%20fires%20a%20NATO%20Sea%20Sparrow%20surface-to-air%20missile%20to%20intercept%20a%20remote-controlled%20drone%20as%20part%20of%20Valiant%20Shield%202016%20(VS16).%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Navy%20photo%20by%20Mass%20Communication%20Specialist%202nd%20Class%20Diana%20Quinlan%2FReleased%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Pentagon%20has%20recently%20prioritized%20combining%20air-defense%20components%20for%20Ukraine%20ahead%20of%20Russian%20strikes%20this%20winter%2C%20all%20under%20the%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fukraine-russia-war-military-missiles-16c344bdba2e0695a2286a55d9614ff4%5C%22%3EFrankenSAM%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20was%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-getting-more-fighter-jets-air-defense-ammo-is-priority-2023-4%5C%22%3Etalked%20about%20in%20leaked%20documents%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Discord%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20Ukraine%20and%20US%20have%20long%20been%20working%20together%20to%20marry%20American%20and%20Soviet%20weaponry.%20Back%20in%20September%202022%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20with%20a%20little%20creative%20engineering%2C%20Ukraine%20equipped%20its%20MiG-29%20fighter%20jets%20with%20AGM-88%20HARM%20missiles.%20The%20US%20weapons%20were%20previously%20incompatible%20with%20Ukraine's%20Soviet%20jets%2C%20but%20apparent%20physical%20and%20operational%20launching%20modifications%20were%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20the%20head%20of%20US%20Air%20Forces%20in%20Europe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbreakingdefense.com%2F2022%2F09%2Fit-took-couple-of-months-to-put-us-anti-radiation-missiles-on-ukrainian-fighters-usaf-reveals%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20%26quot%3Bwas%20quite%20the%20effort%26quot%3B%20integrating%20the%20missiles%20onto%20Ukrainian%20MIGs.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20is%20it%20as%20integrated%20as%20it%20is%20on%20an%20F-16%3F%26quot%3B%20Gen.%20James%20Hecker%20said.%20%26quot%3BOf%20course%20not.%20So%20it%20doesn't%20have%20all%20the%20capabilities%20that%20it%20would%20on%20an%20F-16.%26quot%3B%20But%20it%20worked%2C%20giving%20Ukraine%20the%20ability%20to%20hunt%20enemy%20radars.%3