39706df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222835%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPerformance-improvement%20plans%20don't%20necessarily%20spell%20the%20end%20for%20workers.%3Cp%3Eerhui1979%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPerformance-improvement%20plans%20are%20often%20a%20scary%20thing%20for%20employees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYet%20when%20they're%20set%20up%20fairly%2C%20PIPs%20can%20offer%20a%20chance%20for%20redemption%20and%20growth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMore%20managers%20should%20be%20using%20PIPs%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20as%20an%20ultimatum%2C%20career%20experts%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20were%20just%20told%20you're%20being%20put%20on%20a%20performance-improvement%20plan%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20end%2C%20right%3F%20Time%20to%20update%20your%20LinkedIn%20profile%20and%20start%20applying%20for%20jobs%20ASAP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20answer%20is%20yes.%20Being%20put%20on%20a%20PIP%20is%20often%20a%20warning%20shot%20from%20HR%20that%20you%20might%20soon%20be%20fired.%20Yet%20if%20a%20PIP%20is%20structured%20fairly%2C%20it%20shouldn't%20automatically%20be%20a%20death%20blow%2C%20career%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20even%20recommended%20that%20PIPs%20be%20used%20by%20more%20managers%2C%20provided%20the%20plans%20are%20deployed%20as%20they%20were%20meant%20to%20be%20used%3A%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20enhance%20performance%20or%20help%20an%20employee%20reset%2C%20and%20not%20as%20a%20last-ditch%2C%2090-day%20ultimatum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeanne%20MacDonald%2C%20CEO%20of%20recruitment%20process%20outsourcing%20at%20Korn%20Ferry%2C%20the%20organizational%20consulting%20giant%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20perhaps%2010%25%20of%20employees%20should%20be%20on%20a%20PIP%20at%20any%20one%20time%20as%20a%20way%20to%20help%20workers%20deemed%20less%20effective.%20Among%20those%2C%20a%20good%20chunk%20should%20be%20expected%20to%20come%20off%20the%20plan%20and%20return%20to%20an%20employer's%20good%20graces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20say%20you%20get%20half%20of%20them%20off%20the%20plan%20%E2%80%94%20recovering%2C%20doing%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that's%20what%20good%20looks%20like%2C%20right%3F%20You're%20helping%20people%20to%20kind%20of%20develop%20themselves%20up%20because%20people%20need%20help.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPIPs%20shouldn't%20be%20a%20threat%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Ba%20chance%20to%20work%20through%20the%20plan.%20You%20need%20to%20show%20what%20they%20can%20do.%20And%20I%20love%20it%20when%20someone%20can%20turn%20from%20a%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20MacDonald%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20thinks%20some%20managers%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20waited%20for%20layoffs%20and%20restructuring%20plans%20rather%20than%20using%20PIPs%20to%20move%20out%20weaker%20employees.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20what%20people%20should%20be%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20MacDonald%20said.%20Instead%2C%20she%20said%2C%20bosses%20need%20to%20be%20undertaking%20the%20essential%20and%20sometimes%20difficult%20work%20of%20coaching%20workers%20who%20need%20to%20beef%20up%20their%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPIPs%20can%20be%20a%20good%20thing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPIPs%20instill%20fear%2C%20but%20they're%20actually%20a%20useful%20tool%20to%20help%20someone%20grow%20at%20work%20when%20set%20up%20correctly%2C%20said%20Paul%20Falcone%2C%20management%20consultant%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3B101%20Sample%20Write-Ups%20for%20Documenting%20Employee%20Performance%20Problems.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20he's%20seen%20many%20times%20over%20decades%20working%20in%20HR%20where%20an%20employee%20turns%20it%20around%2C%20comes%20off%20a%20plan%2C%20and%20ends%20up%20a%20more%20valuable%20worker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFalcone%20told%20BI%20employers%20should%20be%20specific%20about%20the%20things%20people%20need%20to%20achieve%20to%20get%20off%20a%20plan.%20%26quot%3BAs%20an%20employer%2C%20you%20are%20obligated%20to%20help%20your%20employees%20succeed.%20You%20can't%20just%20give%20them%20a%20parking%20ticket%20and%20say%2C%20'Here%20you%20go.%20Do%20it%20again%20and%20you're%20fired%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFalcone%20doesn't%20think%20employers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-doubles-target-lowest-performance-ratings-non-regrettable-attrition-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eshould%20target%20a%20percentage%20of%20their%20people%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20improvement%20plans.%20He's%20also%20not%20a%20fan%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-use-cut-low-bad-performers-stack-ranking-harvard-professor-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eso%20called%20rank%20and%20yank%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0when%20employers%20score%20all%20workers%20so%20the%20bottom%20slice%20can%20get%20pushed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20done%2C%20it%20needs%20to%20get%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Falcone%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20cutting%20workers%20only%20when%20the%20need%20arises.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20manufacture%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20looking%20to%20have%20a%20portion%20of%20workers%20on%20PIPs%2C%20he%20said%2C%20managers%20need%20to%20focus%20on%20communicating%20with%20workers%20on%20how%20to%20improve%20so%20that%20when%20a%20PIP%20is%20necessary%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20surprise%20to%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsk%20about%20your%20chances%20of%20surviving%20a%20PIP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20PIPs%20are%20necessarily%20well-intentioned%20efforts%20to%20help%20workers%2C%20of%20course.%20And%20even%20when%20they%20are%2C%20most%20employees%20placed%20on%20these%20plans%20aren't%20going%20to%20be%20happy%20about%20it.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20workers%20have%20said%20they%20felt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-performance-plan-pivot-aws-worker-lost-deposit-on-house-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eunfairly%20targeted%20by%20PIPs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFalcone%20said%20in%20situations%20where%20trust%20between%20workers%20and%20their%20bosses%20seems%20to%20have%20eroded%2C%20a%20PIP%20can%20mean%20it's%20time%20to%20move%20on.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20a%20manager%20is%20fed%20up%20with%20a%20worker%20and%20simply%20wants%20the%20person%20gone.%20It's%20hard%20to%20bounce%20back%20from%20that%2C%20Falcone%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20who%20aren't%20sure%20whether%20the%20PIP%20is%20simply%20a%20penultimate%20step%20to%20getting%20fired%20can%20ask%20and%20see%20what%20kind%20of%20reaction%20they%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20manager%20starts%20looking%20down%20at%20their%20shoes%20and%20they%20won't%20meet%20eye-to-eye%20and%20their%20body%20language%20gets%20all%20crumply%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20start%20folding%20their%20arms%20and%20all%20this%20other%20stuff%20%E2%80%94%20you%20know%20what%3F%20Yeah%2C%20they're%20probably%20going%20to%20say%2C%20'No%2C%20this%20is%20kind%20of%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20Falcone%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20should%20also%20submit%20a%20written%20response%20to%20the%20PIP%2C%20he%20said.%20Doing%20so%20can%20help%20them%20document%20that%20they%20won't%20repeat%20a%20certain%20behavior%20that%20got%20them%20into%20trouble%20or%20it%20can%20let%20them%20tell%20their%20side%20of%20the%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPIPs%20should%20be%20a%20last%20resort%2C%20Danna%20Greenberg%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20organizational%20behavior%20at%20Babson%20College%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNone%20of%20us%20ever%20do%20our%20jobs%20perfectly%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BManagers%20need%20to%20get%20comfortable%20continually%20giving%20feedback%20and%20catching%20people%20when%20they're%20doing%20great%20work%20and%20coaching%20them%20to%20develop%20their%20areas%20of%20weakness.%20And%20if%20you're%20doing%20that%20regularly%2C%20performance-improvement%20plans%20should%20ultimately%20be%20for%20the%20employee%20who%20really%20maybe%20isn't%20well%20suited%20for%20their%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFalcone%20said%20a%20good%20PIP%2C%20used%20judiciously%2C%20can%20help%20both%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20making%20sure%20that%20the%20employee%20understands%20what%20the%20problem%20is%2C%20you%20show%20that%20as%20an%20employer%20you're%20willing%20to%20help.%20They%20usually%20will%20turn%20things%20around.%20It's%20a%20good%20way%20to%20salvage%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20a%20way%20of%20documenting%20people%20out%20of%20a%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-performance-improvement-plan-how-to-survive-career-development-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699991210000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6553bf0e4ca513d824292616%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-performance-improvement-plan-how-to-survive-career-development-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22PIPs%20shouldn't%20be%20a%20threat%20to%20employees%2C%20an%20expert%20said.%20Here's%20why%20PIPs%20can%20be%20a%20good%20thing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40insider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-performance-improvement-plan-how-to-survive-career-development-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Isro%20prods%20youth%20to%20design%20robotic%20rovers%20for%20future%20missions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699991073000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105217506%2Cimgsize-35668.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fisro-pr