raised%20for%20her%20fashion%20sense%20and%20recently%20showcased%20a%20yellow%20lehenga%20on%20social%20media.%20She%20also%20celebrated%20Diwali%20with%20her%20family%2C%20wearing%20a%20heavily%20embroidered%20purple%20suit.%20In%20an%20interview%2C%20she%20discussed%20coping%20with%20disappointments%20at%20the%20box%20office.%20Sara%20is%20set%20to%20star%20in%20Anurag%20Basu's%20upcoming%20film%20'Metro%20In%20Dino'%20alongside%20Aditya%20Roy%20Kapur%2C%20Anupam%20Kher%2C%20and%20others%2C%20which%20is%20set%20to%20release%20on%20March%2029%2C%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fsara-ali-khan-channels-her-inner-jodha-in-a-stunning-yellow-lehenga-radiates-princess-vibes%2Farticleshow%2F105214844.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20Levels%20of%20Fine%20Particulate%20Matter%20Peak%20Post-Diwali%2C%20Air%20Quality%20Drops%20in%20Several%20Cities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F13184606%2FPollution.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Post-Diwali%2C%20several%20Indian%20cities%20have%20shown%20a%20peak%20in%20fine%20particulate%20matter%20(an%20air%20pollutant)%2C%20as%20per%20a%20preliminary%20analysis%20by%20the%20National%20Clean%20Air%20Programme%20(NCAP)%20Tracker%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhich%20tracks%20India%E2%80%99s%20air%20quality%20data%20and%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20NCAP.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFine%20particulate%20matter%20or%20PM2.5%20are%20fine%2C%20inhalable%20particles%20%E2%80%93%20around%202.5%20mm%20in%20diameter%20%E2%80%93%20are%20produced%20due%20to%20the%20emission%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20such%20as%20coal.%20Fireworks%20are%20also%20known%20to%20temporarily%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F1660-4601%2F17%2F24%2F9333%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eincrease%20levels%20of%20PM2.5%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20along%20with%20other%20pollutants%20such%20as%20sulfur%20dioxide%20in%20high%20concentrations.%20Such%20particulate%20matter%20can%20cause%20health%20concerns%20including%20respiratory%20ailments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHigher%20PM2.5%20post-Diwali%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFine%20particulate%20matter%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20considered%20a%20significant%20public%20health%20concern.%20Hence%2C%20PM2.5%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20pollutants%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20government-run%20air%20quality%20monitoring%20stations%20measure.%20According%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpcb.nic.in%2Fupload%2FNAAQS_2019.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECentral%20Pollution%20Control%20Board%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20under%20the%20National%20Ambient%20Air%20Quality%20Standard%20(NAAQS)%2C%20the%20safe%20level%20of%20annual%20PM2.5%20is%20set%20as%2040%20%CE%BCg%2Fm3%20and%20the%2024-hour%20average%20as%2060%20%CE%BCg%2Fm3.%20The%20National%20Air%20Quality%20Index%20also%20lists%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20limit%E2%80%9D%20for%20daily%20average%20PM2.5%3A%200-30%20%CE%BCg%2Fm3.%20The%20revised%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firis.who.int%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F10665%2F345329%2F9789240034228-eng.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eglobal%20air%20quality%20guidelines%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20in%202021%2C%20however%2C%20set%20a%20stricter%20standard%3A%205%20%CE%BCg%2Fm3%20for%20an%20annual%20average%20and%2015%20%CE%BCg%2Fm3%20for%20a%2024-hour%20average.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20NCAP%20Tracker%2C%20a%20policy%20tracker%20that%20keeps%20tabs%20on%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20National%20Clean%20Air%20Programme%20and%20its%20effectiveness%2C%20and%20also%20analyses%20air%20quality%20data%20compiled%20from%20government-run%20monitoring%20stations%2C%20analysed%20the%20daily%20average%20PM2.5%20levels%20across%2011%20cities%20in%20the%20country%20over%20three%20days%20%E2%80%93%20a%20day%20before%20Diwali%20(November%2011)%2C%20the%20day%20of%20Diwali%20(November%2012)%20and%20a%20day%20after%20Diwali%20(November%2013).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%2011%20cities%20are%20Bengaluru%2C%20Bhopal%2C%20Chandigarh%2C%20Chennai%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Gandhinagar%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20Lucknow%2C%20Mumbai%20and%20Patna.%20The%20festival%20of%20Diwali%20is%20marked%20by%20aerial%20fireworks%20in%20most%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%20Studies%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS2590162119300553%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%20one%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202020%20have%20shown%20that%20fireworks%20during%20the%20festival%20days%20%E2%80%9Ccontribute%20to%20an%20increase%20of%20PM2.5%20loading%20in%20Delhi%20significantly%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20NCAP%20Tracker%E2%80%99s%20preliminary%20analyses%20for%20this%20year%2C%20PM%202.5%20levels%20on%20this%20Diwali%20and%20for%20the%2012%20hours%20after%20(till%20noon%20on%20November%2013)%20were%20above%20the%20CPCB%E2%80%99s%20daily%20average%20%E2%80%98good%E2%80%99%20limit%20of%2030%20ug%2Fm3%20in%20all%20the%20cities%20analysed.%20Patna%20in%20Bihar%20showed%20the%20highest%20average%20PM%202.5%20level%20on%20the%20day%20of%20Diwali%202023%20(November%2012)%2C%20at%20206.1%20ug%2Fm3.%20This%20is%20around%2013.7%20times%20more%20than%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20daily%20safe%20limit%20of%2015%20ug%2Fm3.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDelhi%20leads%20in%20spike%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2013%20(from%20midnight%20to%2012%20pm)%2C%20Delhi%20recorded%20the%20highest%20PM2.5%20average%20of%20300.9%20ug%2Fm3.%20Per%20the%20report%2C%20Delhi%20also%20witnessed%20the%20highest%20spike%20(recorded%20at%2015-minute%20intervals)%20%E2%80%93%20at%20999.5%20ug%2Fm3%20at%20Pusa%20on%20November%2013%20at%201%3A30%20am).%20Several%20other%20capital%20cities%20also%20experienced%20extremely%20high%20PM2.5%20levels%20on%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20Diwali%20and%20the%20following%20day%20(November%2013)%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20compare%20levels%20of%20PM2.5%20%E2%80%93%20or%20any%20other%20pollutant%20across%20years%20%E2%80%93%20unless%20other%20confounding%20factors%20are%20at%20play%20such%20as%20wind%20speed%20and%20rainfall%20(which%20will%20affect%20PM2.5%20levels%20and%20make%20it%20vary%20from%20year%20to%20year%20in%20each%20city)%20are%20accounted%20for.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAarti%20Khosla%2C%20director%20of%20Climate%20Trends%2C%20which%20runs%20NCAP%20Tracker%20along%20with%20Respirer%20Living%20Sciences%2C%20suggests%20a%20drastic%20step%3A%20phasing%20out%20the%20firecracker%20industry%20itself%20over%20the%20next%202-3%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CStemming%20supply%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20in%20a%20press%20release%2C%20%E2%80%9Cis%20the%20only%20way%20to%20asphyxiate%20demand%20in%20this%20case.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20Supreme%20Court%20ban%20in%20Delhi%20NCR%20was%20flouted%20fully%20and%20shows%20that%20a%20different%20approach%20where%20the%20centre%20and%20state%20must%20work%20together%20is%20needed%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhasing%20out%20firecrackers%20may%20seem%20an%20extreme%20step%20for%20many%20while%20%E2%80%9Cenvironment-friendly%E2%80%9D%20fireworks%20are%20now%20available.%20These%2C%20according%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.acs.org%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1021%2Facs.est.0c03521%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eresearchers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20emit%2015-65%25%20less%20particulate%20matter.%20However%2C%20the%20researchers%20also%20found%20that%20such%20fireworks%20still%20deteriorate%20air%20quality%20rather%20significantly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThree%20Indian%20cities%20among%20the%20most%20polluted%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20Swiss%20technology%20company%20IQAir%2C%20which%20measures%20live%20air%20quality%20(PM2.5%20levels)%20using%20data%20from%20monitoring%20stations%20and%20sensors%20operated%20by%20a%20range%20of%20organizations%20including%20governmental%20bodies%20and%20research%20institutions%2C%20three%20Indian%20cities%20are%20among%20the%20top%20ten%20cities%20across%20the%20world%20that%20have%20the%20most%20polluted%20air.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20of%203%20pm%20on%20November%2014%2C%20Delhi%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iqair.com%2Fworld-air-quality-ranking%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eleading%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20the%20most%20polluted%20city%20(highest%20PM2.5%20levels%20across%20the%20world)%2C%20with%20an%20Air%20Quality%20Index%20(AQI)%20of%20306.%20The%20AQI%20here%20is%20measured%20based%20on%20WHO%20standards%20and%20the%20ideal%20limit%20is%20an%20annual%20PM2.5%20level%20of%205%20%CE%BCg%2Fm3.%20The%20IQAir%20lists%20an%20AQI%20of%20more%20than%20300%20as%20%E2%80%9CHazardous%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CAt%20this%20extreme%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20health%20warning%20of%20emergency%20conditions.%20The%20entire%20population%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20severely%20affected%2C%E2%80%9D%20per%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iqair.com%2Fnewsroom%2Fhazardous-air-quality%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIQAir%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMumbai%2C%20the%20capital%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20was%20in%20fourth%20place%2C%20with%20an%20AQI%20of%20156%20%E2%80%93%20which%20falls%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunhealthy%E2%80%9D%20category.%20Kolkata%20came%20ninth%2C%20with%20an%20AQI%20of%20127%2C%20which%20is%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunhealthy%20for%20sensitive%20groups%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699973112000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F13184606%2FPollution.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fas-levels-of-fine-particulate-matter-peak-post-diwali-air-quality-drops-in-several-cities%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Patna%20showed%20the%20highest%20average%20PM%202.5%20level%20on%20the%20day%20of%20Diwali%202023%20(November%2012)%2C%20at%20206.1%20ug%2Fm3.%20This%20is%20around%2013.7%20times%20more%20than%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20daily%20safe%20limit%20of%2015%20ug%2Fm3.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fas-levels-of-fine-particulate-matter-peak-post-diwali-air-quality-drops-in-several-cities%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ICICI%20Bank%20recovers%20Rs%20366%20crore%20from%20troubled%20builder%20JP%20Associates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699973066000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-09%2F28%2Ffull%2F1695883865-6682.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ficici-bank-recovers-rs-366-crore-from-troubled-builder-jp-associates-123111401003_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22To%20get%2018.9%20crore%20shares%20which%20was%20pledged%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ficici-bank-recovers-rs-366-crore-from-troubled-builder-jp-associates-123111401003_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ficici-bank-recovers-rs-366-crore-from-troubled-builder-jp-associat