anges%20needed%20to%20either%20restrict%20global%20warming%20to%201.5%C2%B0C%20or%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%2C%20to%20remain%20within%20the%202%C2%B0C%20threshold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFormal%20definition%20of%20COP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormally%2C%20COP%20assumes%20the%20role%20of%20the%20supreme%20decision-making%20body%20within%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fresource%2Fdocs%2Fconvkp%2Fconveng.pdf%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%20Framework%20Convention%20on%20Climate%20Change%3C%2Fa%3E%20(UNFCCC)%2C%20and%20its%20subsidiary%20agreements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UNFCCC%2C%20which%20came%20into%20force%20in%20March%201994%2C%20seeks%20to%20forestall%20perilous%20human%20interference%20with%20the%20climate%20system.%20It%20underscores%20the%20necessity%20of%20achieving%20this%20objective%20within%20a%20time%20frame%20that%20allows%20ecosystems%20to%20naturally%20adapt%20to%20climate%20change%2C%20safeguards%20food%20production%2C%20and%20promotes%20sustainable%20economic%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20objective%20is%20not%20to%20halt%20global%20warming%20entirely%2C%20which%20is%20no%20longer%20feasible%2C%20but%20to%20mitigate%20and%20adapt%20to%20its%20negative%20impacts%20to%20prevent%20greater%20catastrophe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMembership%20and%20decision-making%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20UNFCCC%20boasts%20nearly%20universal%20membership%2C%20with%20198%20countries%20that%20have%20ratified%20the%20convention%20designated%20as%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20COP%20gatherings%2C%20all%20parties%20convene%20to%20scrutinise%20convention%20implementation%20and%20forge%20decisions%20imperative%20to%20its%20effective%20execution%2C%20including%20institutional%20and%20administrative%20arrangements.%20These%20decisions%20are%20included%20in%20COP%20output%20documents%20such%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fprocess-and-meetings%2Fthe-paris-agreement%2Fthe-glasgow-climate-pact-key-outcomes-from-cop26%5C%22%3EGlasgow%20Climate%20Pact%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fdocuments%2F624444%5C%22%3ESharm%20El%20Sheikh%20Implementation%20Plan%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDecisions%20are%20reached%20by%20consensus%2C%20which%20enables%20individual%20nations%20to%20exert%20substantial%2C%20often%20disproportionate%2C%20influence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20significant%20resistance%20has%20emanated%20from%20prominent%20developed%20nations%20such%20as%20the%20US%2C%20Russia%2C%20China%20and%20Australia%2C%20often%20underpinned%20by%20economic%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20part%2C%20this%20is%20because%20the%20convention%20primarily%20assigns%20the%20responsibility%20of%20leadership%20in%20global%20action%20to%20developed%20nations%2C%20which%20have%20consented%20to%20support%20climate%20change%20initiatives%20by%20providing%20financial%20aid%2C%20knowledge%2C%20and%20technology%20to%20less-developed%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20because%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20vulnerable%20nations%20are%20on%20the%20frontline%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20suffering%20disproportionately%2C%20yet%20contribute%20the%20least%20to%20carbon%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20precise%20scope%20and%20mechanisms%20for%20such%20support%20remain%20subjects%20of%20heated%20debate%2C%20with%20the%20Global%20Environment%20Facility%20presently%20overseeing%20a%20system%20of%20grants%20and%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcop27.eg%2F%5C%22%3ECOP27%20in%20Sharm%20El-Sheik%3C%2Fa%3E%20established%20a%20Loss%20and%20Damage%20Fund%20to%20compensate%20less-developed%20nations%20for%20the%20harm%20caused%20by%20emissions%20that%20have%20largely%20come%20from%20industrialised%20nations%2C%20although%20the%20timeline%20for%20its%20operationalisation%20remains%20uncertain%2C%20leading%20many%20to%20fear%20it%20may%20come%20too%20late%20for%20many%20vulnerable%20countries%20and%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrequency%20and%20format%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECOP%20meetings%20convene%20annually%2C%20unless%20parties%20decide%20otherwise.%20The%20inaugural%20COP%20meeting%20was%20held%20in%20Berlin%20in%20March%201995.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rotation%20of%20the%20COP%20presidency%20mirrors%20the%20five%20recognised%20UN%20regions%20(Africa%2C%20Asia%2C%20Latin%20America%20and%20the%20Caribbean%2C%20Central%20and%20Eastern%20Europe%2C%20and%20Western%20Europe%20and%20Others).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20propensity%20for%20the%20venue%20to%20alternate%20among%20these%20groups.%20For%20instance%2C%20Australia%20has%20tendered%20a%20bid%20to%20host%20COP31%20in%202026%20in%20partnership%20with%20Pacific%20Nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20ground%20at%20COP%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20whirlwind%20of%20activity%2C%20divided%20between%20negotiations%20and%20the%20pavilion%20areas%2C%20which%20are%20characterised%20by%20the%20simultaneous%20occurrence%20of%20hundreds%20of%20sessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20negotiations%20predominantly%20centre%20on%20the%20countries%20(parties)%20involved%2C%20leaving%20civil%20society%20participants%20%E2%80%93%20comprising%20researchers%2C%20non-profit%20organisations%2C%20activists%2C%20youth%2C%20Indigenous%20communities%2C%20business%20leaders%2C%20and%20other%20stakeholders%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20periphery%20of%20decision-making%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20stakeholders%20often%20find%20themselves%20stationed%20in%20an%20expo-style%20zone%20adjacent%20to%20the%20formal%20negotiations%2C%20where%20they%20showcase%20their%20work%20and%20attempt%20to%20influence%20proceedings.%20In%20more%20recent%20times%20criticisms%20have%20emerged%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fcop%2Fun-experts-cop27-corporate-climate-pledges-rife-with-greenwashing-2022-11-08%2F%5C%22%3Egreenwashing%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20level%20of%20interaction%20between%20policymakers%20and%20civil%20society%20remains%20limited%2C%20a%20contentious%20issue%20in%20its%20own%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20role%20and%20value%20of%20this%20burgeoning%20civil%20society%20circus%20at%20COP%20has%20become%20the%20subject%20of%20heated%20debate.%20Some%20argue%20it%20inadvertently%20fosters%20greenwashing%20rather%20than%20genuine%20action%2C%20suggesting%20that%20the%20focus%20should%20be%20squarely%20on%20the%20negotiations%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EContrarily%2C%20others%20contend%20it%20provides%20a%20vital%20platform%20for%20civil%20society%20to%20voice%20its%20concerns%20and%20present%20new%20research%2C%20and%20directs%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20media%20spotlight%20towards%20the%20most%20critical%20issue%20of%20our%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20significance%20of%20COP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECOP%20holds%20immense%20significance%20because%20it%20serves%20as%20the%20crucible%20for%20pivotal%20global%20decisions%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Paris%20Agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20inaugural%20COP%20in%20Berlin%20in%201995%20(COP1)%20marked%20the%20commitment%20of%20major%20countries%20to%20annual%20discussions%20on%20climate%20change%20and%20emissions%20reductions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20COP3%20in%20Kyoto%20(1997)%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fkyoto_protocol%5C%22%3EKyoto%20Protocol%3C%2Fa%3E%20emerged%2C%20obliging%20industrialised%20nations%20to%20curtail%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20and%20establishing%20the%20carbon%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECOP13%20in%20Bali%20(2007)%20augmented%20the%20Kyoto%20Protocol%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fprocess%2Fconferences%2Fthe-big-picture%2Fmilestones%2Fbali-road-map%5C%22%3EBali%20Road%20Map%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20involving%20all%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20target%20of%20limiting%20temperature%20rise%20to%20below%202%C2%B0C%20crystallised%20at%20COP15%20in%20Copenhagen%20(2009).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20notably%2C%20COP21%20in%20Paris%20in%202015%20culminated%20in%20the%20unanimous%20adoption%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20by%20all%20nations%2C%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20capping%20global%20temperature%20increases%20at%202%C2%B0C%2C%20ideally%20aiming%20for%201.5%C2%B0C%20(although%20current%20progress%20remains%20sorely%20insufficient).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20the%20UNFCCC%20has%20intensified%20its%20focus%20on%20urgency.%20Instrumental%20in%20this%20has%20been%20the%20work%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcc.ch%2F%5C%22%3EIntergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%3C%2Fa%3E%20(IPCC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IPCC%20was%20established%20in%201989%20as%20a%20joint%20intergovernmental%20initiative%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.wmo.int%2Fen%5C%22%3EWorld%20Meteorological%20Organization%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unep.org%2Fnode%5C%22%3EUN%20Environment%20Programme%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20their%20assessment%20reports%20and%20special%20reports%20have%20been%20key%20in%20precipitating%20significant%20COP%20decisions%20and%20climate%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELoss%20and%20damage%20is%20a%20cross-cutting%20issue%2C%20specifically%20determining%20the%20compensation%20that%20developing%20nations%20should%20receive%20from%20industrialised%20nations%20for%20damages%20incurred%20due%20to%20unsustainable%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EAssociate%20professor%20Susie%20Ho%20is%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Monash%20Innovation%20Guarantee%20in%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20Deputy%20Vice%20Chancellor%20Education.%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EAssociate%20Professor%20Gerry%20Nagtzaam%20is%20a%20world%20recognised%20environmental%20scholar%20whose%20research%20focuses%20on%20the%20intersections%20between%20environmental%20law%2C%20politics%2C%20history%20and%20economics.%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDr%20Sali%20Bache%20is%20the%20international%20policy%20lead%20at%20Climateworks%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20the%20Asia%20Pacific%20region.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EPeter%20Graham%20is%20an%20Associate%20Professor%20in%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.monash.edu%2Fmada%2Farchitecture%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EArchitecture%20at%20Monash%20University%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%2C%20and%20the%20Executive%20Director%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gbpn.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EGlobal%20Buildings%20Performance%20Network%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%2C%20an%20international%20network%20of%20experts%20dedicated%20to%20achieving%20the%20mitigation%20of%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20from%20the%20buildings%20sector.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20article%20originally%20appeared%20in%20%3C%2Fi%3ELens%2C%3Ci%3E%20published%20by%20Monash%20University.%20Monash%20will%20be%20at%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.monash.edu%2Fmonash-at-cop%2Fcop-28%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECOP28%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%20Published%20under%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20by%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%5C%22%3E360info%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699968614000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02214750%2Fimage-1468.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fwhat-is-cop-and-why-should-i-care%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Progress%20on%20climate%20issues%20may%20be%20slow%20but%20COP%20remains%20the%20best%20mechanism%20for%20pressuring%20governments%20to%20make%20the%20changes%20needed%20to%20avert%20catastrophe.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A