odi%E2%80%99s%20comments%20to%20step%20up%20their%20attack%20on%20Nitish.%20The%20development%20has%20surprised%20the%20neutral%20observers%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20the%20ones%2C%20who%20had%20closely%20watched%20the%20situation%20in%20which%20Nitish%20had%20%E2%80%98installed%E2%80%99%20Manjhi%20as%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20owning%20responsibility%20for%20his%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%E2%80%99s%20poor%20performance%20in%20the%202014%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFew%20had%20imagined%20at%20that%20time%20that%20Nitish%20%E2%80%93%20the%20supreme%20leader%20of%20his%20party%20who%20had%20staged%20a%20comeback%20as%20the%20chief%20minister%20after%20securing%20unprecedented%20victory%20for%20the%20JDU-BJP%20alliance%20with%20210%20seats%20in%20243%20member-Bihar%20assembly%20in%202010%20assembly%20polls%20%E2%80%93%20would%20demit%20his%20position%20in%20favour%20of%20someone%20else%20after%20the%20BJP%20had%20done%20well%20in%20the%202014%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20performed%20majestically%20in%20all%20the%20north%20Indian%20states%20in%202014%20and%20Bihar%20was%20not%20an%20exception.%20And%20it%20was%20a%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20fought%20in%20the%20name%20of%20Modi%20against%20the%20Congress.%20In%20no%20way%2C%20Nitish%20could%20have%20been%20made%20accountable%20for%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20poor%20show%20in%20that%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06122347%2FF63GTNNWMAAsSYi.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06122347%2FF63GTNNWMAAsSYi.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06122347%2FF63GTNNWMAAsSYi-300x202.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06122347%2FF63GTNNWMAAsSYi-1024x688.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678572%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22806%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40narendramodi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20in%20Bihar%2C%20and%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20and%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20too%20had%20lost%20massively%20against%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20had%20projected%20Modi%20as%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20and%20Modi%20had%20created%20waves%20in%20his%20favour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2014%20scenario%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20on%20May%2020%2C%202014.%20The%20counting%20of%20votes%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20was%20over%20and%20preparations%20were%20afoot%20for%20Narendra%20Modi%20to%20take%20over%20from%20Manmohan%20Singh%20as%20the%20prime%20minister%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20Nitish%20Kumar%20called%20the%20meeting%20of%20his%20JD(U)%20legislature%20party%20and%20announced%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20own%20the%20moral%20responsibility%20of%20our%20party%E2%80%99s%20defeat%20at%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20and%20quit%20as%20your%20(JDU%E2%80%99s%20legislature%20party%E2%80%99s)%20leader.%20You%20are%20free%20to%20elect%20anyone%20from%20amongst%20you%20as%20your%20leader.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20about%2010%20am.%C2%A0%20All%20the%20JDU%20MLAs%20were%20stunned.%20They%20collectively%20objected%20to%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20decision%20and%20insisted%20on%20him%20not%20to%20do%20it.%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20senior%20from%20the%20JP%20movement%20days%20in%20the%201970s%20and%20then%20state%20JDU%20president%20Bashishtha%20Narayan%20Singh%20was%20miffed%20at%20Nitsh%E2%80%99s%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20then%20party%E2%80%99s%20national%20president%2C%20Sharad%20Yadav%2C%20landed%20in%20Patna%20at%20noon%2C%20driving%20to%20the%201-Aney%20Marg%20%E2%80%93%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20house%20and%20venue%20of%20the%20JDU%20legislature%20party%20meeting%20%E2%80%93%20to%20oversee%20the%20proceedings.%20The%20JDU%20cadres%20who%20had%20thronged%20in%20thousands%20outside%20the%201-Aney%20Marg%20hit%20out%20at%20Sharad%20Yadav%20when%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20persuade%20Nitish%3B%20we%20will%20have%20to%20go%20by%20his%20decision.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20are%20the%20president.%20It%E2%80%99s%20sacrilegious%20that%20you%20are%20unable%20to%20persuade%20Nitish%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Your%20conduct%20is%20not%20acceptable%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20cadre%20was%20heard%20blurting%20angrily%20at%20Sharad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MLAs%20kept%20up%20with%20their%20pressure%20on%20Nitish%20to%20withdraw%20his%20decision%20to%20quit%20as%20the%20chief%20minister%20for%20almost%20five%20hours.%20However%2C%20they%20failed%20eventually%20and%20consented%20to%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20nominate%20someone%20in%20his%20place.%20It%20was%20at%20about%202%3A30%20pm%20Nitish%20dropped%20the%20name%20of%20Jitan%20Ram%20Manjhi%2C%20the%20MLA%20from%20Makhdumpur%20belonging%20to%20the%20Mahadalit%20Musahar%20community%2C%20as%20his%20replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReluctantly%2C%20the%20party%20MLAs%20acquiesced%20to%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20decision%20but%20they%20got%20the%20resolution%20passed%20that%20specifically%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CManjhi%20will%20remain%20CM%20only%20till%20the%20tenure%20of%20the%20present%20assembly%20(2010-2015).%20Nitish%20Kumar%20will%20lead%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20in%20the%202015%20assembly%20elections.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Foolish%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98stupid%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98orphan%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPM%20Modi%20interpreted%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20remark%20that%20his%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Emurkhata%3C%2Fem%3E%20(foolishness)%20led%20him%20to%20make%20Manjhi%20the%20CM%E2%80%9D%20as%20%E2%80%9Cshameless%20and%20humiliation%20to%20Manjhi%E2%80%9D%20which%20the%20Bihar%20BJP%20leaders%20have%20picked%20up%20to%20launch%20a%20frontal%20attack%20on%20Nitish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20fact%20remains%20that%20several%20JDU%20cadres%20were%20angry%20at%20Nitish%20for%20demitting%20office%20in%20Majhi%E2%80%99s%20favour.%20They%20weren%E2%80%99t%20ready%20to%20accept%20it.%20Outside%20the%201-Aney%20Marg%2C%20many%20JDU%20cadres%20were%20heard%20using%20the%20words%20like%20%E2%80%9Cfoolish%2C%20stupid%20and%20obstinate%E2%80%9D%20when%20they%20learnt%20about%20his%20decision%20to%20make%20Manjhi%20the%20chief%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20had%20emerged%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98hero%E2%80%99%20of%20the%C2%A0Mahadalits%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20bloc%20of%20the%20poor%20communities%20which%20he%20had%20given%20preferential%20treatment%20to%20in%20the%20jobs%2C%20panchayat%20raj%20bodies%20and%20a%20plethora%20of%20other%20welfare%20schemes.%20Manjhi%20was%20born%20and%20brought%20up%20in%20a%20Mahadalit%20community.%20But%20no%20Bihar%20leader%20had%20worked%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20Mahadalits%20in%20the%20manner%20Nitish%20had.%20Even%20the%20Mahadalit%20cadres%20of%20the%20JDU%20were%20pained%20at%20Nitish%20getting%20replaced%20with%20Manjhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20himself%20faced%20the%20cadres%E2%80%99%20angry%20outbursts%20when%20he%20escorted%20Manjhi%20to%20governor%20D.%20Y%20Patil%20and%20returned%20to%20stop%20at%20the%20gathering%20of%20the%20exasperated%20cadres%20with%20Manjhi%20by%20his%20side.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20made%20you%20the%20CM.%20Who%20has%20allowed%20you%20to%20subvert%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20mandate%20in%20favour%20of%20your%20personal%20choice%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20angry%20cadre%20shouted%20at%20him.%20Another%20screamed%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%20have%20made%20the%20people%20%3Cem%3Eanaath%3C%2Fem%3E%20(orphan)%20by%20relinquishing%20the%20responsibility%20given%20by%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14165552%2F1500x500.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14165552%2F1500x500.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14165552%2F1500x500-300x100.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14165552%2F1500x500-1024x341.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684733%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJitan%20Ram%20Manjhi%20swearing-in%20as%20chief%20minister%20of%20Bihar%20in%20May%202014.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(Twitter)%2F%40jitanrmanjhi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20cadres%20were%20heard%20using%20%E2%80%9Cfoolish%20and%20stupid%E2%80%9D%20words%20to%20describe%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20decision.%20Nitish%20pacified%20them%20by%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20will%20live%20with%20you%20and%20work%20according%20to%20your%20wishes%20and%20will.%20I%20will%20lead%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20again%20in%202015.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Nitish%20said%20that%20he%20made%20Manjhi%20the%20chief%20minister%20out%20of%20his%20%E2%80%9Cfoolishness%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20was%20merely%20repeating%20the%20words%20that%20his%20cadres%20had%20used%20against%20him%20on%20May%2020%2C%202014.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20the%20pre-Narendra%20Modi%20era%20media%20was%20sympathetic%20to%20Nitish.%20A%20few%20months%20before%20making%20Manjhi%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20Nitish%20vacated%20his%20chair%20for%20Dasrath%20Manjhi%20%E2%80%93%20a%20Mahadalit%20cultivator%20who%20had%20cut%20the%20rocks%20with%20the%20shovel%20and%20spade%20to%20make%20a%20path%20in%20the%20mountains%20of%20Gaya.%20The%20media%20had%20equated%20Manjhi%E2%80%99s%20installation%20with%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20symbolic%20gesture%20for%20Dasrath%20Manjhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EManjhi%E2%80%99s%20U-turn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20making%20Manjhi%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20Nitish%20formed%20the%20Mahagathbandhan%20with%20the%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20and%20the%20Congress%20and%20fanned%20out%20in%20the%20north%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20Champaran%20region%20to%20organise%20the%20electorate%20against%20the%20BJP.%20Jitan%20Manjhi%20stayed%20silent%20for%20a%20few%20weeks%20following%20up%20on%20the%20development%20work%20and%20welfare%20initiatives%20that%20Nitish%20had%20undertaken.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20too%20embarked%20on%20the%20tours%20across%20the%20state%20causing%20embarrassing%20situations%20for%20Nitish%20by%20his%20%E2%80%98bizarre%E2%80%99%20conduct%20and%20utterances.%20At%20a%20public%20meeting%20at%20Darbhanga%2C%20he%20said%20that%20a%20temple%20was%20washed%20after%20he%20offered%20prayer%20in%20it%20and%20was%20found%20wrong%20by%20an%20inquiry%20committee.%20He%20described%20the%20upper%20castes%20as%20%E2%80%9Cforeigners%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20Dalits%20as%20%E2%80%9Caborigines%E2%80%9D%20and%20derided%20the%20lower%20caste%20women%20who%20had%20their%20husbands%20working%20in%20other%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbihar-jitan-ram-manjhi-exit-mahagathbandhan%5C%22%3EBihar%3A%20Jitan%20Ram%20Manjhi%E2%80%99s%20Potential%20Exit%20Will%20Not%20Worry%20the%20Mahagathbandhan%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20JDU%20cadres%20were%20up%20in%20arms%20against%20Manjhi%20parading%20on%20the%20streets%20and%20demanding%20Nitish%20to%20replace%20him.%20But%20when%20the%202015%20assembly%20elections%20drew%20close%20and%20the%20party%20leadership%20demanded%20Majhi%20to%20demit%20the%20office%20in%20favour%20of%C2%A0%20Nitish%2C%20Manjhi%20rebelled%20levelling%20%E2%80%98insult%E2%80%99%20to%20him%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Celitist%E2%80%9D%20JDU.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20after%20a%20long%20and%20strenuous%20effort%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Sharad%20Yadav%2C%20Bashishtha%20Narayan%20Singh%2C%20and%20others%20in%20the%20party%2C%20Manjhi%20stepped%20down%20as%20the%20chief%20minister.%20But%2C%20after%20he%20stepped%20down%20as%20chief%20minister%2C%20Jitan%20Manjhi%20made%20his%20own%20party%20%E2%80%93%20Hindustani%20Awam%20Morcha%20(Secular)%20%E2%80%93%20that%20aligned%20with%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%202015%20assembly%20elections%20against%20the%20Nitish-led%20JDU-RJD-Congress%20Mahagathbandhan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fnalin-verma%26source%3Dgmail-imap%26ust%3D1700462521000000%26usg%3DAOvVaw2-eWIxEMgG1CAj-Gsha6XF%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%253Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fnalin-verma%2526source%253Dgmail-imap%2526ust%253D1700462521000000%2526usg%253DAOvVaw2-eWIxEMgG1CAj-Gsha6XF%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1700030303126000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2L22b2ffNX8A-fCVH8EHgX%5C%22%3ENalin%C2%A0Verma%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%2C%20author%2C%20media%20educator%2C%20and%20independent%20researcher%20in%20folklore.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699964961000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14164628%2FThe-Wire-76.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-modis-counter-to-nitishs-outburst-at-jitan-ram-manjhi-doesnt-reveal-the-full-story%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Modi%20has%20recently%20called%20the%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20'shameless'%20after%20the%20latter%20said%20that%20it%20was%20his%20'foolishness'%20that%20led%20him%20to%20'install'%20Jitin%20Ram%20Manjhi%20as%20the%20chief%20minister%20in%202014%20in%20his%20place.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-modis-counter-to-nitishs-outburst-at-jitan-ram-manjhi-doesnt-reveal-the-full-story%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20The%20Who%E2%80%99s%20Who%20in%20the%20Data%20%7C%20Chamar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14175046%2F4764323306_5a4fa1b6ea_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBeyond%20politics%2C%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%20is%20a%20revolutionary%20document.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20public%20document%2C%20the%20first%20ever%20after%201931%2C%20allowing%20for%20people%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20be%20counted.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20go%20down%20to%20the%20wire%2C%20on%20what%20each%20of%20the%20numbers%20unveiled%20mean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWho%20are%20the%20people%20referred%20to%20by%20percentages%20in%20the%20survey%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EToday%20we%20look%20at%20Chamar%20(6%2C869%2C664%20people)%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20some%20communities%20which%20are%20spread%20in%20every%20corner%20of%20the%20country.%20One%20such%20community%20is%20the%20Chamar%20caste.%20According%20to%20the%20caste-based%20survey%20report%202022%20released%20by%20the%20Bihar%20government%2C%20there%20are%206%2C869%2C664%20people%20belonging%20to%20this%20caste%20in%20Bihar%2C%20which%20is%20about%205.255%20%25%20of%20the%20total%20population.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20political%20presence%20of%20the%20caste%20group%20has%20also%20been%20quite%20significant%20and%20it%20is%20no%20surprise%20that%20Jagjivan%20Ram%2C%20who%20hailed%20from%20this%20caste%20group%2C%20was%20at%20one%20point%20so%20influential%20that%20former%20prime%20minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20used%20to%20address%20him%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBabu%20ji%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20In%201977%2C%20when%20a%20non-Congress%20government%20was%20formed%2C%20he%20was%20made%20the%20deputy%20Prime%20Minister.%20In%20Bihar%20itself%2C%20a%20place%20where%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20castes%20have%20remained%20dominant%2C%20Ramsundar%20Das%2C%20of%20the%20community%2C%20was%20chief%20minister%20from%20April%2021%2C%201979%20to%20February%2017%2C%201980.%20Notably%2C%20this%20was%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Kanshi%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20Bahujan%20movement%20had%20not%20yet%20reached%20Bihar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20346px)%2085vw%2C%20346px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22346%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22496%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20there%20is%20a%20huge%20difference%20between%20political%20and%20social%20consciousness.%20To%20understand%20why%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Chamar%20caste%20group%20are%20mistreated%20even%20today%2C%20there%20is%20need%20for%20deep%20sociological%20reflection.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20development%20of%20human%20civilisation%20is%20a%20continuous%20process.%20None%20of%20its%20phases%20were%20completed%20immediately%20after%20they%20began.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20their%20course%20of%20development%2C%20humans%20adopted%20farming%20after%20hunting%20which%20was%20a%20great%20achievement%20for%20the%20human%20race%20ever%20since%20its%20origin.%20But%20since%20it%20was%20a%20collective%20achievement%2C%20it%20can%20be%20said%20that%20the%20primitive%20ancestors%20of%20all%20the%20people%20who%20have%20ever%20lived%20on%20this%20earth%20were%20farmers.%20In%20India%2C%20the%20remains%20of%20the%20Indus%20Valley%20civilisation%20indicate%20that%20agriculture%20was%20the%20most%20important%20activity.%20People%20carried%20out%20farming%20but%20they%20were%20also%20craftsmen%20who%20moulded%20urban%20civilisation%20in%20their%20own%20respective%20ways.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%20how%20were%20castes%20created%3F%20How%20did%20someone%20become%20a%20cobbler%20from%20a%20farmer%20when%20everybody%E2%80%99s%20main%20occupation%20was%20farming%3F%20This%20is%20a%20question%20which%20has%20not%20been%20discussed%20in%20academia%20enough.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChamars%20are%20historically%20a%20caste%20group%20which%20has%20maintained%20their%20hold%20on%20both%20farming%20and%20craftsmanship%20as%20occupations.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20they%20are%20similar%20to%20carpenters%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebadhai)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eor%20blacksmiths%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Elohar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E).%20Potters%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekumhar)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20can%20also%20be%20included%20in%20this%20category%3B%20they%20made%20utensils%2C%20pitchers%20and%20tiles%20from%20clay.%20Like%20all%20these%20crafts%2C%20the%20craft%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Echamar%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20cobbler%20is%20also%20fascinating.%20The%20people%20of%20this%20caste%20group%20ares%20also%20cattle%20herder%2C%20but%20they%20did%20not%20leave%20the%20corpses%20of%20dead%20animals%20to%20rot.%20They%20rendered%20even%20their%20mortal%20remains%20useful%20and%20it%20was%20owing%20to%20them%20that%20humans%20were%20able%20to%20protect%20themselves%20in%20the%20cold%20season%20by%20covering%20themselves%20with%20skins%20the%20Chamar%20people%20removed%20from%20dead%20animals.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStrangely%2C%20the%20deity%20Shankar%20who%20is%20depicted%20as%20wearing%20the%20skin%20of%20a%20dead%20animal%20is%20worshiped%20by%20people%20of%20this%20country%20but%20the%20very%20people%20who%20have%20removed%20that%20skin%20from%20the%20animal%20and%20turned%20it%20into%20a%20piece%20of%20clothing%20for%20even%20the%20gods%20to%20adorn%20were%20deemed%20%E2%80%98untouchable%E2%80%99.%20Even%20today%2C%20this%20caste%20group%20is%20mistreated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20one%20considers%20unrecorded%20history%2C%20the%20contribution%20of%20Chamars%20in%20farming%20has%20been%20no%20less%20than%20that%20of%20blacksmiths%20and%20carpenters.%20The%20people%20of%20the%20carpenter%20community%20made%20the%20wooden%20plough%2C%20and%20the%20blacksmiths%20smelted%20iron%20to%20make%20the%20plow%20which%20penetrates%20the%20ground%20and%20turns%20the%20soil.%20But%20none%20of%20this%20would%20be%20possible%20if%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Chamar%20caste%20had%20not%20made%20the%20leather%20bag%20which%20is%20used%20in%20the%20bellows%2C%20to%20collect%20air%20and%20thereby%20heat%20the%20coal%20of%20the%20furnace%20so%20that%20it%20melts%20even%20iron.%20It%20was%20an%20amazing%20invention%20about%20which%20nothing%20has%20been%20recorded%2C%20anywhere.%20The%20people%20of%20Chamar%20caste%20appear%20to%20have%20been%20the%20first%20to%20use%20valves.%20They%20learned%20from%20experience%20that%20there%20is%20no%20place%20in%20the%20world%20without%20air.%20Thus%20they%20made%20a%20big%20leather%20bag%20and%20fitted%20a%20valve%20in%20it%20so%20that%20when%20the%20bellow%20was%20lifted%2C%20air%20would%20rush%20in%20through%20the%20valve%20and%20when%20it%20was%20pressed%2C%20the%20valve%20would%20close%20and%20the%20air%20would%20come%20out%20through%20a%20fixed%20path%20and%20increase%20the%20temperature%20of%20the%20burning%20coal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20public%20health%20as%20well%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Chamar%20caste%20have%20made%20a%20significant%20contribution%20by%20saving%20humanity%20from%20various%20epidemics.%20They%20carried%20the%20dead%20bodies%20of%20animals%20out%20of%20the%20village%20area%2C%20a%20practice%20which%20continues%20even%20today.%20Had%20they%20not%20been%20doing%20so%2C%20village%20after%20village%20would%20fall%20victim%20to%20various%20contagious%20diseases.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20caste%20system%20can%20be%20said%20to%20have%20destroyed%20the%20syncretic%20culture%20of%20India%20in%20which%20there%20was%20no%20distinction%20between%20blacksmiths%2C%20carpenters%2C%20potters%2C%20cobblers%20and%20other%20farmer%20groups.%20Whatever%20skill%20a%20person%20had%20was%20used%20and%20it%20laid%20the%20foundation%20of%20a%20developed%20society.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrently%2C%20the%20most%20persecuted%20among%20the%20Dalits%20are%20people%20of%20the%20Chamar%20caste.%20Be%20it%20Rajasthan%20or%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20they%20are%20beaten%2C%20tortured%20and%20killed%20for%20trivial%20reasons%20like%20riding%20horses%20or%20donning%20a%20moustache.%20Even%20today%2C%20the%20stigma%20of%20untouchability%20is%20such%20that%20if%20they%20drink%20water%20from%20an%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20person%E2%80%99s%20pitcher%2C%20they%20are%20killed%20as%20punishment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20political%20consciousness%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Chamar%20caste%20are%20enlightened.%20As%20a%20result%20no%20political%20party%20is%20in%20a%20position%20to%20ignore%20them%20today.%20People%20of%20this%20caste%20no%20longer%20support%20a%20party%20out%20of%20fear.%20Today%20they%20have%20their%20own%20ideology%20which%20was%20inspired%20by%20the%20ideology%20of%20Dr.%20B.R.%20Ambedkar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFamous%20mystic%20poet%20and%20saint%20Raidas%E2%80%99s%20message%20of%20breaking%20the%20caste%20barrier%20is%20an%20inspiration.%20Raidas%20was%20born%20in%20Kashi%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20but%20his%20message%20reached%20far%20and%20wide%2C%20including%20Bihar.%20The%20same%20Raidas%2C%20who%20had%20dreamed%20of%20Begumpura%20and%20had%20said%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSaid%20Raidas%20Khalas%20Chamara%2C%20the%20one%20who%20hails%20from%20that%20city%20is%20a%20friend%20of%20ours.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F260821%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-contributions-of-chamar-caste%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20of%20the%20series%20on%20the%20following%20communities%20by%20clicking%20on%20their%20names%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-ghasi%5C%22%3EGhasi%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3ESantrash%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3EMadaria%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-koeri-kushwaha%5C%22%3EKoeri%2FKushwaha%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chaupal%5C%22%3EChaupal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-nai-hajjaam%5C%22%3ENai%2FHajjaam%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-pasi%5C%22%3EPasi%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-rangrez%5C%22%3ERangrez%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20series%20is%20available%20in%20Hindi%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F260200%2Fbihar-caste-survey-who-are-the-santarash%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20in%20Urdu%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewireurdu.com%2Fauthor%2Fnaval-kishor-kumar%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699964174000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14175046%2F4764323306_5a4fa1b6ea_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chamar%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20group%20can%20be%20said%20to%20be%20the%20most%20persecuted%20among%20Dalits.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chamar%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Supreme%20Court%20Saves%20US%20Boy's%20Life%2C%20Permits%20Indian%20Cousin%20To%20Donate%20Liver%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20come%20to%20the%20rescue%20of%20a%20three-year-old%20boy%2C%20a%20US%20citizen%20in%20critical%20need%20of%20liver%20transplant%2C%20by%20permitting%20his%20distant%20Indian%20cousin%20to%20donate%20the%20organ%2C%20saying%20it%20is%20not%20an%20appropriate%20case%20to%20consider%20the%20legal%20requirement%20in%20%E2%80%9Cabsolute%20terms%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaking%20it%20clear%20that%20its%20decision%20will%20not%20be%20treated%20as%20%E2%80%9Cprecedent%20for%20any%20other%20case%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20top%20court%2C%20in%20a%20compassionate%20verdict%2C%20accorded%20primacy%20to%20saving%20the%20life%20of%20the%20child%20who%20was%20admitted%20to%20a%20private%20hospital%20in%20Gurugram%20for%20treatment%20of%20decompensated%20biliary%20cirrhosis%20(DBC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20DBC%20is%20a%20medical%20condition%20which%20results%20from%20liver%20failure%20and%20a%20patient%20can%20be%20saved%20by%20the%20transplant%20only.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20comprising%20justices%20A%20S%20Bopanna%20and%20M%20M%20Sundresh%20was%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20legal%20challenge%20in%20the%20form%20of%20section%209%20of%20the%20Transplantation%20of%20Human%20Organs%20and%20Tissues%20Act%20(THOTA)%20which%20was%20coming%20in%20the%20way%20of%20liver%20donation%20to%20the%20child%20by%20his%20distant%20Indian%20cousin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20section%20of%20THOTA%20bars%20transplant%20of%20organs%20where%20recipient%20is%20a%20foreigner%20and%20donor%20is%20not%20a%20%26quot%3Bnear%20relative%26quot%3B.%20The%20term%20--%20%26quot%3Bnear%20relative%26quot%3B%E2%80%94%20includes%20%26quot%3Bspouse%2C%20son%2C%20daughter%2C%20father%2C%20mother%2C%20brother%2C%20sister%2C%20grandfather%2C%20grandmother%2C%20grandson%20or%20granddaughter%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20cousin%20is%20not%20included%20in%20the%20definition%20of%20%26quot%3Bnear%20relative%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20took%20note%20of%20the%20submissions%20of%20senior%20advocate%20Gopal%20Sankarnarayanan%20and%20lawyer%20Neha%20Rathi%2C%20who%20appeared%20for%20the%20petitioners%20--%20the%20recipient%20and%20the%20donor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%2C%20in%20its%20November%209%20order%2C%20noted%20the%20details%20of%20the%20case%20and%20the%20report%20of%20the%20authorisation%20committee%20which%20functions%20under%20the%20THOTA%20and%20authorises%20the%20transplant%20of%20organ%20if%20the%20donor%20and%20the%20recipient%20comply%20with%20the%20statutory%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20the%20outset%2C%20we%20clarify%20that%20though%20the%20provisions%20as%20contained%20in%20The%20Transplantation%20of%20Human%20Organs%20and%20Tissues%20Act%2C%201994%20as%20also%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%20was%20referred%20to%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20submissions%20on%20either%20side%2C%20in%20our%20opinion%2C%20the%20instant%20case%20would%20not%20be%20an%20appropriate%20case%20to%20consider%20the%20same%20in%20detail%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20note%20of%20immediate%20necessity%20of%20a%20donor%20to%20donate%20the%20liver%20to%20child%20in%20view%20of%20his%20precarious%20health%20condition%20and%20asked%20the%20parties%20to%20go%20through%20the%20legal%20process%20as%20contemplated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%2C%20the%20reasons%20have%20also%20been%20ascertained%20as%20to%20why%20the%20parents%20of%20the%20petitioner%20No.%201%20(recipient)%20have%20not%20donated%20the%20liver.%20Though%20specific%20reasons%20have%20not%20been%20disclosed%2C%20it%20would%20be%20appropriate%20to%20take%20note%20of%20the%20sentiment%20of%20the%20mother%20of%20the%20petitioner%20No.%201%20and%20in%20that%20regard%2C%20exempt%20the%20parents%20in%20any%20event%20since%20in%20the%20instant%20case%20there%20is%20an%20appropriate%20donor%20who%20is%20a%20relative%20and%20since%20this%20Court%20is%20also%20satisfied%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20bona%20fides%20in%20this%20case%20and%20in%20the%20peculiar%20circumstance%20where%20the%20choice%20for%20this%20Court%20is%20between%20saving%20the%20life%20of%20three%20years%20old%20child%20i.e.%20the%20petitioner%20No.1%20or%20adherence%20to%20the%20legal%20requirement%20in%20absolute%20terms%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20in%20the%20peculiar%20facts%20and%20circumstances%20of%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20the%20order%20permitting%20the%20distant%20cousin%20to%20donate%20liver%20cannot%20be%20treated%20as%20a%20precedent%20for%20any%20other%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%202%2C%20the%20bench%20had%20deferred%20the%20hearing%20on%20the%20plea%20seeking%20its%20approval%20for%20liver%20donation%20by%20a%20person%20to%20a%20three-year-old%20cousin%20suffering%20from%20chronic%20liver%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20was%20listed%20before%20the%20bench%20after%20Chief%20Justice%20D%20Y%20Chandrachud%20took%20note%20of%20the%20urgency.%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20Aishwarya%20Bhati%20was%20asked%20to%20assist%20the%20bench%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20child%2C%20who%20is%20a%20US%20citizen%20and%20OCI%20(overseas%20citizen%20of%20India)%20card%20holder%2C%20is%20suffering%20from%20liver%20failure%20and%20needed%20to%20undergo%20a%20transplant%20to%20save%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20parents%20of%20the%20child%20were%20declared%20unfit%20for%20donation%2C%20the%20cousin%20volunteered%20but%20section%209%20of%20the%20law%20was%20coming%20in%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699964160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-06%2Fi0lrb1n_doctor-generic_625x300_28_June_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-saves-us-boys-life-permits-indian-cousin-to-donate-liver-4573358%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20come%20to%20the%20rescue%20of%20a%20three-year-old%20boy%2C%20a%20US%20citizen%20in%20critical%20need%20of%20liver%20transplant%2C%20by%20permitting%20his%20distant%20Indian%20cousin%20to%20donate%20the%20organ%2C%20saying%20it%20is%20not%20an%20appropriate%20case%20to%20consider%20the%20legal%20requirement.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news